===Etymology 1===
From {{der|hu|trk|-}} (compare {{cog|tr|sav}}), possibly through {{inh|hu|urj-ugr-pro|*sawɜ}} (compare Northern Mansi {{m|mns|сов}}, Northern Khanty {{m|kca|сӑв}}).

====Noun====
{{hu-noun|pl=szavak|alt=szók}}

# {{lb|hu|linguistics}} [[word]] {{gloss|smallest unit of language which has a particular meaning}}
# [[word]] {{gloss|promise; oath or guarantee}}
#: {{uxi|hu|Sosem szegjük meg a '''szavunkat'''.|We never break our '''word'''.}}
# [[voice]] {{gloss|an expressed opinion, choice, will, desire, or wish; the right or ability to make such expression or to have it considered}}
#: {{uxi|hu|[[Népszava|Nép'''szava''']]|The '''Voice''' of People|q=title of a newspaper}}
# [[sound]]
#: {{uxi|hu|muzsika'''szó'''|'''sound''' of music}}

=====Usage notes=====
''Szók'' as a plural form is mostly used in linguistic terminology, in compounds, e.g. {{m|hu|kötőszók}}. In all other cases, ''szavak'' is preferred.

